            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>The Control Panel is a separate FastAPI router at /control-panel with auth on every request via X-Admin-Token header. When an admin calls POST /config/apply, the flow is: validate each key against ConfigCatalog, write to OverlayStore, then call RuntimeManager.reload() which rebuilds RuntimeService thread-safely with RLock. All changes go to audit_log.jsonl with actor, timestamp, changed keys, and previous values. Overlays are separate .md files for prompts and agents, so we keep source code clean and admin customizations separate. If anything fails during reload, we restore the original os.environ — no half-applied state corruption.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
